          "value": "Three second-hand dressers, worn and maybe white, stand side by side under a small shelter. Each has somewhere between five and eight drawers. Each drawer holds something from childhood, a plastic animal, a note that says something someone's mother once believed, a report card, a friendship bracelet, a matchbox with something inside it, a sticker sheet half-used. Objects that once felt enormous and now fit in the palm of your hand.\n\nThe theme is the things we believed completely, and then quietly stopped believing. Not with bitterness. With the particular tenderness of remembering yourself before you knew better. Santa. That adults have it figured out. That your best friend would be your best friend forever. That you were special in the way you thought you were special.\n\nEvery drawer is different. Some are lined with fabric and gold leaf. Some are sparse. Some are strange. Many are weird and silly. There is no order to them, no right way to explore. You just open things. And maybe something else closes.",
