        {
          "value": "We may host the occasional small party or happening, but overall our sound will remain low - mostly soft background music to support the atmosphere. We aim to be respectful of our neighbors.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Sound levels"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "We will not use any kind of open flames in our camp other than incense. All light sources will be electrical. We will have fire blankets at the ready.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Safety"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "We arrive during the weekend to build, and everything will be taken down during sunday, according to Leave No Trace.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Strike plan"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "We are open to co-creating offerings that align with our vibe of sensuality, calm, and magic. We are part of Agrabah Village - a coalition of _One Thousand and One Nights_\\-inspired aesthetic camps. With extended funding, we will have space to host workshops, happenings, and co-created experiences within our expanded area.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Co-creation"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "Yes. Enough to power a light and music system and kitchen.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Electricity"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "**The Genie’s Lamp is inspired by the world of _One Thousand and One Nights_ - a dream of what it might feel like to step inside a Genie’s lamp.**\n\nAn intimate oasis of sensuality, where satin fabrics drape from the ceiling, soft plush pillows invite you to sink in, and the scent of incense lingers in the air. As you enter, you are welcomed by the Djinn - enchanting, playful, and otherworldly beings who inhabit this space.\n\nStep inside, and you may find it hard to leave… perhaps even forever under their spell.\n\nWe create an aesthetic sanctuary of calm, connection, sensuality, and beauty. Here, the Djinn weave subtle magic, gently playing with the senses and inviting you to slow down, soften, and explore.\n\nWe delight in praise and flattery… and if you charm us just right, you might even be granted a wish.  \n  \n**With extended funding,** The Genie’s Lamp can expand to include a dedicated space for workshops, dance, and intimate gatherings - inviting deeper participation and co-creation within the oasis.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Description"
          }
        }
