        {
          "value": "This project is by nature spontaneously interactive with other dreams.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Co-creation"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "The Babes of Baghdad are a team of nondescript individuals bringing a much needed measure of cheeky pranks and/or tasteful political awareness to the fields of the Borderland.\n\nTheir anonymity represents the presence and force of unheard and unseen (often female) voices in societies around the world - and in ours.\n\nThe Babes of Baghdad do not speak, for they have not been given permission - but you will see their actions speak louder than all those voices whose self-proclaimed right to dominance grants them space in the heard, seen, and explicit.\n\nPractically speaking, the plan is to buy 5 pieces of authentic Burqas, in order to give the babes their proper attire and so make their mission(s) possible.\n\nQualitatively speaking, the idea is to utilize the presence of an extremely powerful symbol, extremely opposite to the surrounding environment, in order to give some perspective onto the often underappreciated lavishness and freedom that the visitors of the Borderland enjoy during the week - and hopefully lead to an increased awareness both of the oppression which is rife in our world, and of our luckily being spared it. Beyond, of course, the purely humorous element.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Description"
          }
        }
