      "id": "cmnudxt1i000wcakyy51ssl6s",
      "title": "Dreamer’s Maze 2.0",
      "summary": "Dreamer´s Maze is an immersive interactive art experience, located in the Villa: 3 floors, 15+ rooms designed by different artists, connected by secret passages",
      "status": "IDEA",
      "noOfFunders": 0,
      "noOfComments": 0,
      "percentageFunded": 171.95,
      "minGoal": 60360,
      "maxGoal": 164990,
      "income": 103790,
      "images": [
        {
          "small": "https://res.cloudinary.com/dreamswtf/image/upload/c_scale,q_90,w_740/v1775915225/dreams/dqafihcjujmqbugysvo4.jpg"
        },
        {
          "small": "https://res.cloudinary.com/dreamswtf/image/upload/c_scale,q_90,w_740/v1775915436/dreams/b6akhpgar46lusr7wv3i.jpg"
        },
        {
          "small": "https://res.cloudinary.com/dreamswtf/image/upload/c_scale,q_90,w_740/v1775915984/dreams/npbiwknrpzfrca2tmrnd.png"
        },
        {
          "small": "https://res.cloudinary.com/dreamswtf/image/upload/c_scale,q_90,w_740/v1775916018/dreams/rybfkjyo5vyxtrcshdvy.jpg"
        },
        {
          "small": "https://res.cloudinary.com/dreamswtf/image/upload/c_scale,q_90,w_740/v1775916039/dreams/qlcz6zhag3zfb0ypqcat.jpg"
        },
        {
          "small": "https://res.cloudinary.com/dreamswtf/image/upload/c_scale,q_90,w_740/v1775916062/dreams/pwlorgb8x955boo8stnv.jpg"
        },
        {
          "small": "https://res.cloudinary.com/dreamswtf/image/upload/c_scale,q_90,w_740/v1775916118/dreams/nijitmfhvn3jtycptzr6.jpg"
        },
        {
          "small": "https://res.cloudinary.com/dreamswtf/image/upload/c_scale,q_90,w_740/v1775916157/dreams/l9xjsp0y7glhyp7ffmdb.jpg"
        }
      ],
      "customFields": [
        {
          "value": "Dreamer’s Maze",
          "customField": {
            "name": "This dream belongs to camp:"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "Dreamer´s Maze is coming back to the Villa!  \nnew artists, new art, new secret passages!\n\nDreamer´s Maze is an immersive interactive art experience. The Maze is located in an existing three-floor abandoned Villa. Each room is designed by different artists, and the floors of the Villa are interconnected with secret passages built by the Maze crew.\n\nAn art maze is a medium in which the distinction between the artists and the visitors dissolves. In the maze, everyone can be part of the art.\n\nOnce you enter, you are in the reality of the Maze, until you exit back to the Playa. As one goes through this Alice-In-Wonderland-like realm, the perception within the Maze can bring up strong emotions or stimulate out-of-the-box thoughts of new neural pathways.\n\nAs you walk, crawl & climb through different rooms, countless emotions may surge through your veins within the out-of-this-world reality of a Maze.\n\nBe aware, you may get lost within the Maze, or you may find yourself… but don’t you worry or be weary, there is light at the end of the tunnel. Follow the unknown path and let your curiosity flourish.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Description"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "feel free to reach out to me on Whatsapp, Facebook or Discord.\n\nDerin Evcim @derinevcim +31649551187",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Designated Dr. Bill-Bull (treasurer of the dream)"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "Last year we were next to the Sanctuary. It wasn’t ideal due to amount of people coming in and sliding out of the Maze towards the direction of the Sanctuary. There were no major concerns, but we were in close contact with the Sanctuary team just in case. This year Sanctuary is planned to be moved to another location. That would mean the Villa is pretty isolated otherwise. We attracted passers by on their way to Muumimaa last year. With Muuimins taking a well deserved break, we are hoping some other legend would take their place at the Muuimins nest and we could be neighbors. We also cherished our neighborly relations with the Power Team, as some camped next-door :)",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Co-existence"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "Last year, we had parties in the Boiler Room, located at the basement of the Villa, This year, we plan to bring the Boiler Room back and it may get loud! Basement of the Villa is well sound isolated.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Sound levels"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "Last year we used around 10kW of electricity. We estimate similar power usage this year.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Electricity"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "We have a new fire engineer onboard. The capacity of the maze will be checked during opening hours. The structure of the Villa will be checked by a licensed professional to deem it safe for use.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Safety"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "The way we approach Dreamer´s Maze is by prioritizing co-creativity. Every Borderling who shares the passion for the Maze is welcome to join co-creating Dreamer´s Maze 2.0. Your idea could bring the Maze to another level!\n\nThe Maze grows like a living entity by the touch of each artist. Your idea could make the difference in bringing that new angle.\n\nMaze art often aims to transform the room it takes place in, so you may feel like you are within art, roaming around inside a painting or maybe in a video game.\n\nMaze crew has a growing theme. This year, a distinctive clothing style is shaping up. We wanna grow our lore further. It could be a story, LARP, immersive theater. Maybe a game, puzzle, escape room, or a riddle? Perhaps a hidden gem, treasure, deep within the Maze.\n\nLast year more than 100 people were involved in Dreamer’s Maze at Borderland 2025!\n\nPeople involved in realizing Dreamer’s Maze 2025:  \n• Maze core team  \n• Maze artists  \n• Carpenters  \n• Power team  \n• Fire safety team  \n• Amsterdam Fire Jam  \n• Our camp & home: Pan-Delirium  \n• The camp 40ish Thieves  \n• Many other friends & camp members of Maze Artists  \n• Fund33 team  \n• Countless others who volunteered to help build the Maze & clean the Villa\n\nLast year most of the art within the maze was interactive, combining art with technology and sensors, so Maze literally reacted to the visitors.\n\nAs our passion and ambitions kept juicing new ideas and creations, plus playa kept giving, Maze shaped up around the visitors, continued enhancing beyond build, each day during the event, basically until strike.\n\nApart from exploring the Maze and its many hidden chambers, visitors were able to craft, paint with a spin-art-machine, solve an escape room puzzle, be a part of an interview, create visuals by dancing, play the piano, make lights with a keyboard, interact with alien tentacles, make bubbles resonate in different frequencies of sound, and even dj at the boiler room! On top of that, overall the immersive spaces within the maze can make you feel part of the maze as you are within the art yourself.\n\nThis year apart from maze artists and builders, we will need support of the community to run the maze. To make sure the maze is safe for everyone, we have at least 4 people on shift per hour the maze is open.\n\n1.  Gate: to brief people and keep the safety capacity in check\n    \n2.  Clown: sober awareness shift, going around inside the maze\n    \n3.  Fluffer: making sure people at gate and clown shifts are doing ok, substituting if necessary\n    \n4.  Lead: Overall responsible person for the maze\n    \n\nIf you wanna be a part of the Maze Crew in BL26, feel free to reach out to me on Whatsapp, Facebook or Discord.\n\nDerin Evcim @derinevcim +31649551187",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Co-creation"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "The Strike starts on Sunday, lasts until the LNT is complete. Last year the strike lasted until Tuesday night after Borderland. We also join Borderland Strike meetings and collaborate with Borderland Strike lead.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Strike plan"
          }
        }
      ],
