          "value": "A small cloud drifting between the trees.\n\nThe smell of freshly brewed coffee. Soft laughter.\n\nSomeone handing you a cookie like it’s the most\n\nimportant ritual of the day. That’s probably us.\n\nCome closer. Imagine being in the clouds. Enjoy\n\nchai, coffee, and cookies that taste like care, baked\n\nwith love, served with presence and compassion.\n\nTell us a secret. Tell us nothing.\n\nMaybe we talk about the universe. Maybe we talk\n\nabout mushrooms, heartbreak, dreams or why the\n\nforest feels alive tonight. Maybe we just sit\n\ntogether while time forgets to exist.",
