      "customFields": [
        {
          "value": "Evelina",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Designated Dr. Bill-Bull (treasurer of the dream)"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "Of course, we are all connected through the underground mycelium that keeps us together.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Co-creation"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "Nothing Suspicious Here",
          "customField": {
            "name": "This dream belongs to camp:"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "Natural moving mob that will leave no trace.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Strike plan"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "The mob will naturally assemble in an unknown place, at an unknown time. It will only last a few minutes, so make sure you don't miss.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Co-existence"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "Mushrooms don't have sound. They will only follow the rhythm which will be played at an appropriate level at appropriate places.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Sound levels"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "Some mushrooms are toxic, we are not.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Safety"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "Self-powered by a large battery that needs electricity to charge. We will use the electricity from the camp",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Electricity"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "Something stirs in the in-between. A nudge, a pull. Threads link up where they shouldn’t. Forms emerge — soft, suspiciously in sync. Coincidence? Unlikely.  \nThey follow something no one admits exists, slipping into patterns that repeat, ripple, and return. A sequence. A rhythm. Bodies aligning for a moment, then dissolving again.\n\nTime gets a little wobbly. So do the edges. It’s playful. It’s precise. It’s already happening. Like mycelium beneath the surface, something connects us — quietly, completely.\n\nAnd sometimes, if you’re there at the right moment… you’ll see it.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Description"
          }
        }
      ],
