        {
          "value": "All electronics packed and transported back. Furniture returned or repurposed. Perishable food consumed or disposed of responsibly.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Strike plan"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "Know your way around Raspberry Pi networking, LED control, or retro game setup? Want to co-host as game master? Get in touch: [jns.johansson@gmail.com](mailto:jns.johansson@gmail.com)",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Co-creation"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "Speakers for background music and game audio at moderate volume. Headphones available for full immersion during gameplay.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Sound levels"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "Located in the earth cellar, naturally sound-isolated. Headphones available for gameplay. Speakers at moderate volume. Minimal impact on surroundings.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Co-existence"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "BorderLAN is back, but different. In 2025, it lived above ground. In 2026, it moves into the earth cellar and becomes a performance piece: a faithful recreation of a LAN party from 2002.\n\nGuests descend into the cellar to find a makeshift basement living room. A couch, rugs, lamps, posters on the walls, and four gaming stations scattered across the space. Some sit at tables, some on the couch, one might be perched on a crate with a monitor on a couch table. Upon arrival, the game master, your host for the evening, hands you the dress code: hoodie and sweatpants. You put them on. You sit down. The ritual begins. Game on!\n\nTwo menus are presented. The food menu features the finest in LAN cuisine: Billy's Pan Pizza, Gorby's Piroger, and an assortment of classic snacks. To drink: a curated selection of perfectly aged beverages, remnants from the early 2000s; Jolt Cola, Dr. Pepper, Glocken Gold. The game menu offers multiplayer classics: Quake III Arena, Counter-Strike 1.6, Age of Empires 2, ActionQuake, StarCraft, Worms, and more.\n\nPart installation, part LARP, part fine dining. A portal back to 2002, served with a napkin over the arm.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Description"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "No",
          "customField": {
            "name": "This dream belongs to camp:"
          }
        }
