      "title": "Fever Night, A Dreamy Drama by the Fuckery",
      "summary": "Live music, sexy actors and a dark erotic story — ending where the stage dissolves and the audience becomes part of the show.\n",
      "status": "IDEA",
      "noOfFunders": 0,
      "noOfComments": 0,
      "percentageFunded": 363.63,
      "minGoal": 5500,
      "maxGoal": 8000,
      "income": 20000,
      "images": [
        {
          "small": "https://res.cloudinary.com/dreamswtf/image/upload/c_scale,q_90,w_740/v1776027283/dreams/p3zklm20mbvwlb2sgbsp.jpg"
        },
        {
          "small": "https://res.cloudinary.com/dreamswtf/image/upload/c_scale,q_90,w_740/v1775736436/dreams/g2dfera4bt2jb7yihykt.jpg"
        },
        {
          "small": "https://res.cloudinary.com/dreamswtf/image/upload/c_scale,q_90,w_740/v1775736461/dreams/eikedca2hsizk9m33zcp.jpg"
        }
      ],
      "customFields": [
        {
          "value": "**The Fuckery**",
          "customField": {
            "name": "This dream belongs to camp:"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "A perfect part of a bustling avenue in the plaza, making the night feel alive for the passers by.\n\nThe show will happen inside the main event tent of the Fuckery camp—a broader play space designed with care and consent at its core. We will clearly communicate our operating hours. We aim to harmonize with nearby camps and spaces, avoiding overlap with events that might clash in vibe or volume. We are open only during scheduled times to preserve possibilities for other events and activities within the space.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Co-existence"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "elatively high, except for the risk bodily fluids that might land on some too closely seated spectators…",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Safety"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "We operate in alignment with The Fuckery's soundscape and sound levels. Music and amplified voices might be heard.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Sound levels"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "Will go down with the rest of The Fuckery, we build Sat-Monday July 19th-20th and are done with Strike no later than Sunday July 26th.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Strike plan"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "Lights and sound; this dream relies on electricity estimations of The Fuckery’s infrastructure, in coordination with the camp team.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Electricity"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "@Mirja is our Dr. Bill-Bull, and is easiest found on the Discord!",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Designated Dr. Bill-Bull (treasurer of the dream)"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "This is theatre. This is seduction. This is The Fuckery on stage.\n\nInspired by Arthur Schnitzler's _Dream Story_ — the same source material that gave us _Eyes Wide Shut_ — Fever Night is a melodramatic, sensual, darkly playful live performance staged on The Erotic Theatre.\n\nThe story: a shadowy secret cult. An innocent initiate. A young lover, desperate to save her from a fate worse than death. And somewhere in the candlelight — you.\n\nExpect live music. Expect dramatic text drawn from seriously classic material, retold with a modern twist. Expect beautiful, barely-dressed performers, a hint of song, a whisper of dance — and a grand finale that blurs the line between stage and audience, launching the evening into its next, real-life chapter.\n\nThe Fuckery team takes the stage. You take your seat. And by the end — we're all part of the show.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Description"
          }
        },
        {
          "value": "Starting with the audience immersed into the world of the play, but in the safety of the spectator role. Ending with the audience invited to merge with the perfomers and start of the evenings play night.",
          "customField": {
            "name": "Co-creation"
          }
        }
      ],
